      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 37: The new JSON parser path calls `asString()` whenever `pt` is present, but this JSON is client-controlled. If a malformed value such as an array/object is provided, JsonCpp can throw/assert instead of rejecting only that field. Please validate the type before reading it, matching the defensive handling used for other optional JSON data.\n\n```suggestion\n+    if (val.isMember(VALUE_KEY_PUSHTYPE)) {\n+        const auto\u0026 pt \u003d val[VALUE_KEY_PUSHTYPE];\n+        if (pt.isString())\n+            pushType \u003d pt.asString();\n+    }\n+\n```",
